    {
      "id": "UgyTDIobhWywQdQAYsR4AaABAg",
      "author": "@AmazingGlobalDiscoveries",
      "authorImage": "https://yt3.ggpht.com/T2v50f6Jyxr5W4Rgq36zJV5ZHEJoK26sCLPrt8u9s0ecJuedWFhcgw42MdyvKjOVmgzbVSm3Qw=s48-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj",
      "text": "Truly a hidden European gem! ❤ Belgrade gets all the fame, but Uvac Canyon and Tara National Park are where the real magic happens. Seeing the griffon vultures over the meanders is something you never forget. Go beyond the capital, people!",
      "likeCount": 6,
      "publishedAt": "2026-07-18T03:15:00Z",
      "replyCount": 0,
      "replies": []
    },
    {
      "id": "Ugz3cGDSXjqNahNhMgF4AaABAg",
      "author": "@globerealife",
      "authorImage": "https://yt3.ggpht.com/JrOXykHjA_tVj5o_Mu4n05K1k3qXBjjqO0UlCZCvaqLUKcESEOnvOZuxtZ4467w0OVrzG53CyQ=s48-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj",
      "text": "The stark contrast between Belgrade’s energetic, non-stop nightlife and the quiet reality of a nation losing 98 residents every single day to demographic decline is deeply sobering.",
      "likeCount": 5,
      "publishedAt": "2026-07-18T02:58:28Z",
      "replyCount": 2,
      "replies": [
        {
          "id": "Ugz3cGDSXjqNahNhMgF4AaABAg.AZOHFxUuGt-AZS4OtzgvjP",
          "author": "@vladanng",
          "authorImage": "https://yt3.ggpht.com/ytc/AIdro_m7hbXxg6QXntdivpSHzknTM65HGT1pO3csm6i3bdQ=s48-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj",
          "text": "In fact, Serbia birth rate even without the migrants western countries have is bigger than those in Western countries, it's just we dont have that scale of imigrants and big amount of population is old one, which is  dying. Many countries face this, and many more will become like this, even Turkey, in next 10/15 years (Etnic Turks have lower birth rate than Serbians today believe it or not, but the country is still growing (slowly), because of Kurds huge birht rate, also Arabs to some extent. Etc etc. As many migrants now come to Serbia, i think in 10/15 y, decline will stop.",
          "likeCount": 0,
          "publishedAt": "2026-07-19T14:23:04Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "Ugz3cGDSXjqNahNhMgF4AaABAg.AZOHFxUuGt-AZS4C30StFR",
          "author": "@vladanng",
          "authorImage": "https://yt3.ggpht.com/ytc/AIdro_m7hbXxg6QXntdivpSHzknTM65HGT1pO3csm6i3bdQ=s48-c-k-c0x00ffffff-no-rj",
          "text": "Well yes, it's not the only one, Western countries even decline more in ethnic group (much more, most of them), it's just them get many migrants (Which now is happening in Serbia). You see this in small towns, villages, where mostly it's old people, Belgrade dont see it, it still growing, it's now one of most visited cities in Balkan (after Istanbul, Athens, and alongside with Bucharest), 100k Russians come to country (not in oficial statistics), and there is big diaspora evertyhere returning for few weeks in country. So in Belgrade and Novi Sad you cannot see any decline, nor will you see, in next years, decades.\n\nIn villages, small town, you can see this shit.",
          "likeCount": 0,
          "publishedAt": "2026-07-19T14:21:19Z"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "Ugwj-Jd486nT5pqyTVx4AaABAg",
